Drawing children you have to watch out for some rules to adhere to. Children have special properties, specifically in proportions. The younger they are, the larger their head size as compared to their body. Thus, if a 20 year old is say... 5  heads tall, an 8 year old would be about 3 and a half heads tall. Just estimates.<br>
<br>
As for facial features children generally also have larger features than adults. This means larger noses, larger mouths, larger eyes. <br>
